company_summary_description:
L is the global leader in tactical loyalty campaigns for grocery retailers. 

Our campaigns are designed to deliver Total Store Impact for our clients. They significantly boost sales productivity and margin across the entire store assortment in the short term while strengthening the retailer’s brand and strategy in the long term. 

Every year, we partner with 100+ top grocery retailers across 35 markets and 5 continents, representing €500B+ in sales. We reward 60M+ customers and deliver a proven +3.8% incremental sales uplift for our clients.

Innovation is at the forefront of our business. We leverage the latest AI technologies to give our clients a competitive edge. Today, our Founders share over 2,500 years of loyalty experience. Our Founder’s Mindset means everyone thinks and acts like the company is their own. 

With Total Store Impact, we continue to deliver what few can: driving sales growth today while building lasting brand equity for the future.

Hi! :)
My name is Constanza, I'm Venezuelan/Argentinian with 10+ years of experience supporting technical, sales, and customer teams in adopting new systems, processes, and tools. Skilled in coordinating cross-functional launches, configuring solutions to operational needs, and training diverse teams to ensure successful implementation. Experienced in retail, customer experience, and digital solutions with the ability to bridge technical workflows and user adoption. 

Fluent in Spanish, English, and Portuguese, with international experience across Europe and Latin America.

company_summary_description:
ELNOR is an edtech startup that provides English learning materials and personalized tutoring to adults living in refugee camps. People in camps are amongst the most disadvantaged in the world, and while their immediate needs of food, shelter, and safety are the focus of international entities and governments, education welfare remains overlooked as a necessity. We believe that language learning allows for self-expression for those who are seeking relief and brings professional and social opportunities when establishing a new life.

ELNOR has begun a pilot program with a group of adults in Europe’s largest refugee camp, Moria, which after the fire in September 2020 has been relocated to other areas of the Greek island of Lesbos. Many people living in refugee camps have very limited access to formal modes of education, and the COVID-19 disruptions put them at a greater disadvantage as it disconnected them from in-person volunteer tutors while they have limited access to internet and electronic devices to participate in virtual learning programs.

Adapting the technology to fit the needs and wifi connectivity of our students, we have been innovating ways that we can connect with them and expand our services to reach more people within Moria and beyond.

profile_summary:
As a Founder and CEO of Many Moneil Branded Companies I help busy professionals and investors free up their time and diversify their portfolio with exceptional opportunities in senior living, multifamily,, hotels and disruptive sectors. With over 40 years of experience in real estate investing, I have a proven track record of delivering consistent cash flow, asset appreciation, and tax benefits to my investors. I have also authored three books on apartment syndication, positivity, and senior living sharing my insights and strategies with thousands of readers.

In addition to Moneil Senior Living I am also the Founder, CEO, and Principal of Moneil Investment and Management Groups & Multifamily Syndication Academy, where I oversee a portfolio of over 8,000 doors and $1 billion in assets under management. I specialize in acquiring, renovating, rebranding, and operating B-class value-add multifamily properties, hotels, and senior living facilities across the US. I am passionate about educating and mentoring others who want to create passive income and a lifestyle they can enjoy through real estate investing. 

Vinney's journey began with a leap of faith onto the shores of America, with nothing but a dream and $7 in his pocket and to pursue MBA at George Washington. He went door to door selling educational books & bibles 13 hours a day. In the heart of Northern California, he found more than a place to call home; he discovered a canvas for his aspirations. This is where Vinney ventured in the vibrant world of real estate.

At age 26, he was a portrait of contrasts: broke, unemployed, yet fiercely optimistic. His journey was not a smooth sail; it was punctuated with challenges that tested his resolve. A memorable incident was when he faced a significant investment setback, yet, with unyielding discipline and perseverance, he turned it into a learning experience. These moments weren't just setbacks; they were stepping stones.

Vinney's pursuit wasn't just for success; it was for a life crafted by his own design. Teaming up with friends and partners, he ventured into real estate with a smile that was contagious. They didn't just build properties; they built dreams.

In less than 16 years, Vinney's vision crystallized into one of the top private real estate investment firms. He wasn't just founding over 10 companies; he was crafting legacies. His story is more than a tale of success; it's a blueprint of turning hope into reality.

company_summary_description:
The Quarto Group (LSE: QRT) is the leading global illustrated book publisher. 

Our mission is to make and sell great books that entertain, educate and enrich the lives of adults and children around the world. 

Quarto creates and owns proprietary content, publishing books from a diverse portfolio of imprints that are creatively independent and expert in developing long-lasting content across specific niches of interest.

We sell books across 50 countries and in 40 languages through a variety of traditional and non-traditional channels, while constantly looking for new ways to create and deliver content that people need.

Quarto employs c. 330 talented people in the US, UK and Hong Kong. The Group was founded in London in 1976. It is domiciled in the US. 

For more information, visit www.quarto.com or follow us on Twitter at @TheQuartoGroup.

company_summary_description: E’ un movimento di opinione indipendente senza scopi di lucro, nato per promuovere, coordinare e sostenere le iniziative delle donne che operano nel campo delle arti, delle professioni e degli affari. In Italia conta circa 11.000 socie,  suddivise in circa 300 Sezioni.  FIDAPA aderisce alla International Federation of Business and Professional Women - BPW, presente in 95 Paesi del mondo. Obiettivi di FIDAPA BPW Italy sono: valorizzare le competenze delle socie indirizzandole verso attività sociali e culturali che favoriscono il miglioramento della vita, anche lavorativa, delle donne; incoraggiare le donne a un continuo impegno e a una consapevole partecipazione alla vita sociale, amministrativa e politica;  essere portavoce delle donne presso le Organizzazioni e le Istituzioni nazionali, europee ed internazionali. Fin dalla sua fondazione nel 1929, FIDAPA  si adopera per rimuovere ogni forma di discriminazione a sfavore delle donne, sia nell'ambito della famiglia sia in quello del lavoro, nel pieno rispetto delle norme vigenti in materia di pari opportunità. Questi obiettivi vengono perseguiti attraverso l’organizzazione di convegni, tavole rotonde, seminari, incontri, progetti, nonché mostre e premi.   FIDAPA BPW Italy è presente è presente nel Comitato Parità presso Il Ministero del Lavoro e delle Politiche Sociali e nella Lobby Europea delle donne.  BPW gode di status consultivo presso il Consiglio Economico e Sociale delle Nazioni Unite e di status partecipativo presso il Consiglio d’Europa, ha le sue rappresentanti nelle più importanti organizzazioni internazionali, tra cui UNESCO, UNICEF e FAO.   https://it-it.facebook.com/fidapamb

company_summary_description:
We are revolutionising business in Ghana and improving the way service is conducted and given throughout Ghana. SearchLocal allows you to see businesses based on location for example a painter in Osu, you’ll then be able to see all painters in this geographic based on review score. The platform allows you to interact with genuine tradespeople / businesses. We have been collecting data not present on Google or online for years, my teams have been in the streets conducting the research and interviewing people one by one. 

Our mission is to connect the industry to the consumer no matter where they are in Accra first and foremost. Having access to reliable and accountable tradespeople at a competitive price in a swift manner. This will greatly put women and the underrepresented on the map!

Furthermore there are challenges facing tradespeople and artisans - Minimal budget, No digital presence, Relying on Word of mouth, lack of digital reviews on their services which our platform seeks to mitigate. In doing so minimizing exposure to rogue tradespeople. 

Platform Features
-Submit jobs locally for artisans to bid on. For example paint my house in Osu.
-Search for artisans by location , category and review score.
-Bid on jobs listed on the platform
-Payment System exists for customer to pay artisan via SearchLocal for complete peace of mind.
-Analytics and Insights - Tools for tracking performance and customer engagement
-Algorithms to match posted jobs to tradespeople and artisans
-Comprehensive Profiles: Detailed profiles with reviews and ratings.
-10,000s of Data items that has been collected over the years. Covering the job disciplines mentioned earlier in point 1.

The APP and Website are in the final stages and we will be launching the platform very soon. Do stand by 🫡

Any further questions or enquiries , please reach Jason Adjalo on 0551863389

profile_summary:
Seasoned Entrepreneur and Business Leader with a proven track record in founding and scaling successful companies across diverse industries. As Founder and CEO of ONESTOP Company for Training, Development, and Consulting, I leverage my extensive experience to drive growth, innovation, and exceptional client outcomes.

My expertise spans strategic leadership, business development, training, consulting, and financial management. I have a passion for building high-performing teams, fostering a culture of excellence, and delivering tailored solutions that address complex business challenges.

Throughout my career, I have consistently demonstrated a strong ability to identify market opportunities, navigate dynamic environments, and achieve sustainable growth. With a focus on client satisfaction, operational efficiency, and ethical business practices, I am committed to making a positive impact on organizations and communities.

profile_summary:
I was born in Viareggio (LU), and I studied in Parma. I have an MD in Law and MA in Trade Marketing Management both at Parma University in 1995 and 1999.
I worked inside the Italian Mass Market Retail from 1996, before as a manager from the producer’s side, then from the retail side.
In 2005 together with some friends, we set up the first Italian ON Line Magazine around Mass Market Retail: “GDONews” even if, during the following years, I worked also as a strategic consultant for some well known Italian retail companies.

GDONews, actually, is one of the most well known Magazine around the italian Mass Market and it is an operative partner of Fiere di Parma Cibus, the most important Trade Fair of italian food
